	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The loose scales you need are the red ones and are stackable.  You can get them off of curscale wolves (not pups) and higher.  You can also occasionally buy them if someone else was kind enough to sell some to a vendor.  This is good becasue at level 6 wolves con yellow (to my SK anyway)<BR>
<BR>
Hunting the wolves is good xp but can be mighty boring... there seems to be long periods where the wolves just stop spawning.  When they do spawn they can be found in the bone pit and in a small valley you can reach by following the left hand wall from the city entrance.  There are usually Scalebones and Giant Scorps hanging around the wolf areas... unless you can con them be sure to avoid the scalebones.. you can ignore the scorps.. even though they con high aggro they always seem to ignore me.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
