	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Shestar's Scaled Coif -<BR>
AC 4 weight 0.8<BR>
Class: WAR CLR PAL RNG SHD DRU MNK BRD ROG SHM<BR>
Race: ALL<BR>
<BR>
Personally I sell this item for 3pp, usually to players levels 3-11.  It's a good item, very low weight, good AC, and it looks really cool, especially on monks in robes.  (I've heard that they look like banded on any other race.)  I saw someone sell one for 6pp once and it made me cringe, it's not really worth that much.  The loose scales can be obtained in about 20 minutes of fighting things you're going to fight anyway, and the 5gp is a low investment.  I once made and sold 7 of these in one evening on Karana, made a bunch of newbies happy.  Though now I'm on Terris-Thule (send me a tell!) and I'm not going to have as many customers there.  I imagine I could sell one for around 8-10pp if I took it to the mainland, but I'd have to get lucky and the trip's not worth that much to me.<BR>
<BR>
The first three I made were all successes, no failures at 1 smithing skill.  Now I have 25 and I average one failure per coif somehow.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
